olarship he was captain of the  varsity baseball team president of his junior and senior class as well as president of the interfraternity council and phi sigma nu fraternity he graduated with an accounting degree in  he entered the army and was assigned to the army audit agency in washington dcnick started his accounting career with arthur andersen in 8 he met and married his wife maryann in 62 and settled in bergen county new jersey after he received his cpa certificate in new york and new jersey he went on to fairleigh dickenson university and completed his mba in financeaccounting graduating magna cum laude nick became a partner of arthur andersen accounting firm in 68 while in new york he was responsible for the retail apparel and fashion industry programafter retiring from arthur andersen in 6 he served on the board of seven public and private companies he last served as a board member of spok a public company in the communications and software industry he was also a member of the conservancy of southwest florida where he served nine years on their audit committeenick was a loyal fan of the ny mets and season ticket holder of the ny football giants attending every home game with his wife and two sons he and maryann were avid golfers and enjoyed a  year membership at hackensack golf club in oradell new jersey upon moving to naples in 6 nick and maryann became one of the founding members of colliers reserve country clubnick will be greatly missed by his loving family and a wonderful group of caring and devoted friends he truly believed life was gooda funeral mass will be celebrated on monday december   at 0 am in saint william catholic church 60 seagate drive naples fl in lieu of flowers donations may be made to christ child society of naples po box 7 naples fl 3407 or avow hospice  whippoorwill lane naples fl 340online condolences may be made by visiting wwwfullernaplescom published in daily record from nov  to nov 2  read more listen to obituary remember share